<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     LIGHTSHIP L1 — SECTION 10: SCRUM EXECUTION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-ls-10">
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:16px">§10 · Scrum Execution — Hybrid Water-Scrum-Fall</div>
  <p class="section-intro">Lightship uses a hybrid approach: Stage-Gate phase structure provides the governance backbone for hardware certification, while Scrum governs day-to-day execution within each phase. This captures the auditability of gated development while preserving agile adaptability.</p>

  <!-- Scrum Framework Table -->
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:12px">Scrum Framework — Roles, Events, Artifacts</div>
  <div class="grid3" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="box">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.12em;margin-bottom:10px;text-transform:uppercase">Accountabilities</div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px">
        <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:5px;padding:9px;border-left:2px solid #63b3ed"><div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#f7fafc;margin-bottom:2px">Product Owner</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0">Maximises product value; owns and orders the Product Backlog</div></div>
        <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:5px;padding:9px;border-left:2px solid #9f7aea"><div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#f7fafc;margin-bottom:2px">Scrum Master</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0">Accountable for Scrum being understood &amp; enacted; serves the team</div></div>
        <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:5px;padding:9px;border-left:2px solid #68d391"><div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#f7fafc;margin-bottom:2px">Developers</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0">Committed to a usable Increment every Sprint; self-organising</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;color:#f6ad55;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.12em;margin-bottom:10px;text-transform:uppercase">Events</div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px">
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:#cbd5e0"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Sprint</strong> — 2-week time-box; all work occurs here</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:#cbd5e0"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Sprint Planning</strong> — defines Sprint Goal + Backlog</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:#cbd5e0"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Daily Scrum</strong> — 15 min; inspect progress; adapt plan</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:#cbd5e0"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Sprint Review</strong> — inspect outcome with stakeholders</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:#cbd5e0"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Retrospective</strong> — inspect how last Sprint went</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;color:#68d391;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.12em;margin-bottom:10px;text-transform:uppercase">Artifacts</div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px">
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:#cbd5e0"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Product Backlog</strong> — emergent ordered list of work; single source of truth</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:#cbd5e0"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Sprint Backlog</strong> — Sprint Goal + selected items + delivery plan</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:#cbd5e0"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Increment</strong> — concrete stepping stone; must meet DoD</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Three Pillars -->
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:12px">Three Pillars of Empiricism — Lightship Application</div>
  <div class="grid3" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="box" style="border-left:3px solid #63b3ed">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px">TRANSPARENCY</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.65">Sprint backlogs and burn-down charts visible to all teams and leadership. DFMEA, RTM, and V&amp;V status shared at every Sprint Review. Impediments tracked in the public Impediment Log — no hidden blockers.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="box" style="border-left:3px solid #9f7aea">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#9f7aea;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px">INSPECTION</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.65">Sprint Reviews demonstrate working increments to stakeholders. Test results reviewed immediately. Phase gate scorecards provide formal inspection of all design and process artifacts at key programme milestones.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="box" style="border-left:3px solid #68d391">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#68d391;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px">ADAPTATION</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.65">ECRs formalise design adaptation from test feedback. Sprint Retrospectives adapt team process. Backlog refinement continuously re-orders work. Schedule and budget forecasts updated monthly.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Waterfall vs Scrum -->
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:12px">Scrum vs. Traditional Waterfall — Why Scrum for Hardware?</div>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto;margin-bottom:20px">
    <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:12px">
      <thead><tr style="background:#1a202c"><th style="padding:9px 14px;text-align:left;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#718096;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">Dimension</th><th style="padding:9px;text-align:center;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#fc8181;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">Traditional Waterfall</th><th style="padding:9px;text-align:center;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#68d391;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">Scrum (Lightship)</th><th style="padding:9px 14px;text-align:left;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#718096;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">L1 Example</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr style="background:#2d3748"><td style="padding:8px 14px;color:#cbd5e0;font-weight:600">Planning horizon</td><td style="padding:8px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:#fc8181">Full project upfront; changes require re-baseline</td><td style="padding:8px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:#68d391">Sprint-by-sprint; plan continuously refined</td><td style="padding:8px 14px;font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0">ECR-001 (aft taper) triggered by actual wind tunnel results — not upfront analysis</td></tr>
        <tr style="background:#1e293b"><td style="padding:8px 14px;color:#cbd5e0;font-weight:600">Feedback loops</td><td style="padding:8px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:#fc8181">End of project or major phase — 6–12 months between learnings</td><td style="padding:8px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:#68d391">Every 2 weeks at Sprint Review + daily standup</td><td style="padding:8px 14px;font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0">BMS firmware bug (ECR-023) caught in Alpha-2 at Sprint Review — ~6 months earlier than waterfall would have</td></tr>
        <tr style="background:#2d3748"><td style="padding:8px 14px;color:#cbd5e0;font-weight:600">Risk visibility</td><td style="padding:8px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:#fc8181">Risks tracked in document; schedule risk often invisible until too late</td><td style="padding:8px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:#68d391">Impediment log reviewed daily; burn-down makes risk visible in real time</td><td style="padding:8px 14px;font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0">CATL cell delay (IMP-001) surfaced and resolved within one sprint via expedited freight</td></tr>
        <tr style="background:#1e293b"><td style="padding:8px 14px;color:#cbd5e0;font-weight:600">Change handling</td><td style="padding:8px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:#fc8181">Costly; requires extensive documentation before approval</td><td style="padding:8px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:#68d391">Expected; incorporated via backlog refinement and ECRs within days</td><td style="padding:8px 14px;font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0">Beta-2 window upgrade (ECR-045) identified mid-program; rapid incorporation without re-baselining full plan</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Five Values -->
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:12px">Five Scrum Values — L1 Application</div>
  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);gap:10px;margin-bottom:20px">
    <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;text-align:center;border-top:3px solid #63b3ed"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px">COMMITMENT</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.55">Teams commit to Sprint Goals. Engineers commit to DoD. Team committed to Gate 4 even under Ford test schedule pressure.</div></div>
    <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;text-align:center;border-top:3px solid #9f7aea"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#9f7aea;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px">FOCUS</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.55">Engineers protect focus time from ad-hoc requests. Impediments escalated to Scrum Master. Single prioritised backlog per squad.</div></div>
    <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;text-align:center;border-top:3px solid #f6ad55"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#f6ad55;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px">OPENNESS</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.55">Ford F-150 Lightning failure (21.4% vs &lt;20% target) immediately surfaced to leadership. Budget overruns reported without sugarcoating.</div></div>
    <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;text-align:center;border-top:3px solid #68d391"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#68d391;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px">RESPECT</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.55">Engineers trusted as domain experts; estimates respected, not overridden. Retrospective feedback treated as constructive.</div></div>
    <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;text-align:center;border-top:3px solid #fc8181"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#fc8181;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px">COURAGE</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.55">Ford range failure raised as Gate 4 blocker (IMP-004). CATL delay escalated to exec within 24 hours. DFMEA authored honestly.</div></div>
  </div>

