═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-ls-17">
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:16px">§17 · Design Failure Mode &amp; Effects Analysis (DFMEA)</div>
  <p class="section-intro">The DFMEA identifies potential design failure modes, their effects, causes, and current controls, driving corrective actions before design is released. DFMEA v1 begins at Gate 2 (PDR); must be closed at Gate 3 (CDR). RPN = Severity × Occurrence × Detection.</p>

  <!-- RPN scale explainer -->
  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:12px;margin-bottom:20px">
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;border-left:3px solid #fc8181">
      <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#fc8181;margin-bottom:6px">Severity (S) · 1–10</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6">1 = no effect → 10 = catastrophic (injury/death). <strong style="color:#fc8181">SEV ≥ 9: corrective action REQUIRED</strong> regardless of RPN.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;border-left:3px solid #f6ad55">
      <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#f6ad55;margin-bottom:6px">Occurrence (O) · 1–10</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6">1 = virtually impossible → 10 = near certain. O ≥ 7 warrants review even with low Severity.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;border-left:3px solid #63b3ed">
      <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#63b3ed;margin-bottom:6px">Detection (D) · 1–10</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6">1 = certain detection before customer → 10 = no detection method. D=10 + SEV≥7 = mandatory action.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="background:#1a2332;border:1px solid #2b6cb0;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;margin-bottom:20px;font-size:12px;color:#a0aec0">
    <strong style="color:#63b3ed">Action Threshold:</strong> RPN ≥ 80 <em>OR</em> SEV ≥ 9 — whichever triggers first. SEV = 10 items require documented action or formal safety case regardless of RPN value.
  </div>

  <!-- DFMEA system selector -->
