<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ §26 SYSTEM SAFETY ENGINEERING ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-ls-26">
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:16px">§26 · System Safety Engineering</div>
  <p class="section-intro">The L1 is a battery-powered, road-towed vehicle carrying occupants at highway speeds in a high-voltage electrical environment. Safety engineering systematically identifies and mitigates hazards that could cause injury, death, or property loss. Safety requirements are derived from formal hazard analysis, allocated to the FRS, and verified through dedicated test cases.</p>

