<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ §28 CONFIGURATION MANAGEMENT ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-ls-28">
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:16px">§28 · Configuration Management</div>
  <p class="section-intro">Configuration management ensures the design, software, hardware, and documentation are accurately defined, controlled, and traceable at every stage. Without CM, the program cannot answer the most critical gate question: <em>"exactly what is the configuration of the product we just tested?"</em></p>

  <!-- Three baselines -->
  <div class="grid3" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:10px;padding:18px;border-left:3px solid #fc8181">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="color:#fc8181">FBL — Functional Baseline</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#718096;margin-bottom:6px">Established at Gate 2 (PDR)</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6">Approved PRS and FRS — defines what the product shall do. All downstream design decisions must trace to the FBL.</div>
      <div style="margin-top:8px;font-size:10px;color:#718096">Controls: PRS + FRS docs; all Level 1 requirements; acceptance criteria</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:10px;padding:18px;border-left:3px solid #f6ad55">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="color:#f6ad55">ABL — Allocated Baseline</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#718096;margin-bottom:6px">Established at Gate 3 (CDR)</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6">System architecture and subsystem requirements — defines how function is allocated to HW, SW, and subsystems.</div>
      <div style="margin-top:8px;font-size:10px;color:#718096">Controls: FRS subsystem allocations; ICD revisions; DFMEA baseline; V&V test plan</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:10px;padding:18px;border-left:3px solid #68d391">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="color:#68d391">PBL — Product Baseline</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#718096;margin-bottom:6px">Established at Gate 4 (Pilot)</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6">Complete released design at pilot production — drawings, BOM, software, test results, and regulatory submissions.</div>
      <div style="margin-top:8px;font-size:10px;color:#718096">Controls: All released drawings (Rev C+); production BOM; SW release version; all V&V test reports</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SW/HW version matrix -->
  <div class="box" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="eyebrow-sm">SW / HW Version Alignment Matrix</div>
    <p style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;margin-bottom:12px;line-height:1.6">Mixing SW versions and hardware revisions is a safety and quality risk. This matrix governs which SW can be flashed to which hardware revision.</p>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto">
      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:11px;min-width:600px">
        <thead><tr style="background:#1a202c">
