          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:center;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">CURRENT RELEASE</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">COMPATIBLE HW</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">QUALIFICATION STATUS</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:center;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">OTA-ELIGIBLE?</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody id="cm-fw-tbody"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Per-VIN record fields -->
  <div class="box" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="eyebrow-sm">Per-Unit VIN Configuration Record — Fields</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:8px;margin-top:8px">
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;min-width:100px">VIN</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5">17-digit NHTSA-format identifier. One-time at production start.</div></div>
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;min-width:100px">Production BOM</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5">BOM-L1-Rxx at time of FAT sign-off. Set at FAT completion.</div></div>
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;min-width:100px">Battery Pack Serial</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5">Pack serial + BOM-PACK-Rxx. Set at pack installation.</div></div>
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;min-width:100px">SW/FW at Ship</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5">All 6 SW components at ship-state. Updated on each OTA event post-delivery.</div></div>
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;min-width:100px">FAT Sign-off</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5">Date and tech ID of final acceptance test. Set at FAT completion.</div></div>
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start"><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#63b3ed;font-weight:700;min-width:100px">OTA History</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5">Log of all OTA events: version, date, success/fail/rollback. Continuous post-delivery.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="center"><button class="btn btn-blue" onclick="showPanel('ls-33')">Next: §33 Risk Management Pillar →</button></div>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ §33 RISK MANAGEMENT PILLAR ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-ls-33">
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:16px">§33 · Risk Management Pillar</div>
  <p class="section-intro">Risk management integrates three streams that are typically siloed: program risks (schedule, cost, scope), engineering risks (DFMEA/PFMEA failure modes), and supply chain risks. Siloing produces contradictory risk pictures. The Risk Management Pillar creates a single integrated risk picture reviewed at every gate.</p>

  <!-- Three streams -->
  <div class="grid3" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;border-top:3px solid #63b3ed">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="color:#63b3ed">Program Risk</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5;margin-bottom:6px">Schedule variances; scope changes; resource availability; budget overruns; external events</div>
      <div style="font-size:10px;color:#718096">Owner: Program Manager · Tool: Jira (P-RISK-xxx)</div>
      <div style="margin-top:6px;font-size:10px;color:#fc8181">Escalation: Any HIGH risk without mitigation plan; gate slip &gt; 2 weeks</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;border-top:3px solid #f6ad55">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="color:#f6ad55">Engineering Risk (DFMEA/PFMEA)</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5;margin-bottom:6px">Design failure modes (DFMEA) + manufacturing process failure modes (PFMEA)</div>
      <div style="font-size:10px;color:#718096">Owner: Chief Engineer + Quality · Cross-ref to DFMEA §17 + PFMEA §20</div>
      <div style="margin-top:6px;font-size:10px;color:#fc8181">Escalation: SEV ≥ 9 without closed action; RPN &gt; 80 without mitigation</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#1e293b;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;border-top:3px solid #68d391">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="color:#68d391">Supply Chain Risk</div>
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.5;margin-bottom:6px">Single-source dependencies; LLI availability; supplier financial risk; geopolitical disruption</div>
      <div style="font-size:10px;color:#718096">Owner: VP Supply Chain · Cross-ref to Supply Chain Register §21</div>
      <div style="margin-top:6px;font-size:10px;color:#fc8181">Escalation: HIGH risk with buffer &lt; 4 months; VSG not on schedule</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Integrated risk register -->
  <div class="box" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:12px">Integrated Risk Register — Top 15 Risks</div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:14px;flex-wrap:wrap">
      <button class="btn btn-sm btn-blue" onclick="filterRisks('all')" id="risk-btn-all">All (15)</button>
      <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#2d3748;color:#a0aec0" onclick="filterRisks('Program')" id="risk-btn-Program">Program (6)</button>
      <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#2d3748;color:#a0aec0" onclick="filterRisks('Supply')" id="risk-btn-Supply">Supply (5)</button>
      <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#2d3748;color:#a0aec0" onclick="filterRisks('Eng')" id="risk-btn-Eng">Engineering (4)</button>
      <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#742a2a;color:#fc8181" onclick="filterRisks('HIGH')" id="risk-btn-HIGH">HIGH (6)</button>
      <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#7b341e;color:#f6ad55" onclick="filterRisks('MEDIUM')" id="risk-btn-MEDIUM">MEDIUM (7)</button>
    </div>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto">
      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:11px;min-width:700px">
        <thead><tr style="background:#1a202c">
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">RISK ID</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">STREAM</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">DESCRIPTION</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:center;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">LEVEL</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">MITIGATION</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:center;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">TARGET CLOSE</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">OWNER</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody id="risk-register-tbody"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="center"><button class="btn btn-blue" onclick="showPanel('ls-25')">Next: §25 Service, Support &amp; Lifecycle →</button></div>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ §25 SERVICE, SUPPORT & LIFECYCLE ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-ls-25">
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:16px">§25 · Service, Support &amp; Lifecycle</div>
  <p class="section-intro">Serviceability is a design requirement, not an afterthought. For a $125K–$145K product with a 10-year expected service life, the ability to diagnose remotely, repair in the field, access spare parts, and safely update firmware are as product-critical as aerodynamic performance.</p>

  <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:16px;flex-wrap:wrap">
    <button class="btn btn-sm btn-blue" onclick="showService('tiers')" id="svc-btn-tiers">Service Tiers</button>
    <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#2d3748;color:#a0aec0" onclick="showService('repair')" id="svc-btn-repair">Repairability Reqs</button>
    <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#2d3748;color:#a0aec0" onclick="showService('spares')" id="svc-btn-spares">Spare Parts Strategy</button>
    <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#2d3748;color:#a0aec0" onclick="showService('diag')" id="svc-btn-diag">Field Diagnostics</button>
    <button class="btn btn-sm" style="background:#2d3748;color:#a0aec0" onclick="showService('ota')" id="svc-btn-ota">OTA Safety Requirements</button>
  </div>
  <div id="service-content" class="box" style="min-height:200px"></div>
  <div class="center" style="margin-top:20px"><button class="btn btn-blue" onclick="showPanel('ls-30')">Next: §30 Sales &amp; Service Readiness →</button></div>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ §30 SALES & SERVICE TRAINING ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-ls-30">
  <div class="eyebrow-sm" style="margin-bottom:16px">§30 · Sales &amp; Service Readiness Training</div>
  <p class="section-intro">A technically excellent product fails commercially if the sales network cannot articulate its value proposition. For the L1, the sales conversation requires explaining electric range impact, LFP battery longevity, OTA updates, and HV safety — topics requiring trained staff, not generic RV dealership product knowledge.</p>

  <!-- Sales readiness -->
  <div class="box" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="eyebrow-sm">Sales Readiness Workstream</div>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto;margin-top:8px">
      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:11px">
        <thead><tr style="background:#1a202c">
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">ASSET / ACTIVITY</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">CONTENT SUMMARY</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">OWNER</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:center;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">TARGET</th>
          <th style="padding:8px 10px;text-align:center;color:#718096;font-size:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #4a5568">GATE</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody id="sales-tbody"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Technician training -->
  <div class="box" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="eyebrow-sm">Service Technician Training — 3 Certification Levels</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:12px;margin-top:8px">
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:16px;border-left:3px solid #63b3ed">
        <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#63b3ed;margin-bottom:4px">Level 1 — Module Swap</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:#718096;margin-bottom:8px">2-day in-person + online pre-work · Gate 4</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Scope:</strong> 12V systems; HMI OTA; HVAC module; cassette toilet; water system; HMI screen<br><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Authorization:</strong> All service except HV battery</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:16px;border-left:3px solid #f6ad55">
        <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#f6ad55;margin-bottom:4px">Level 2 — HV-Adjacent</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:#718096;margin-bottom:8px">1-day add-on to L1 + supervised practicum · Gate 4</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Scope:</strong> HV safety awareness; BMS board swap (interlock prevents HV exposure); diagnostic tablet deep scan<br><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Authorization:</strong> BMS board + diagnostics; must escalate HV battery events</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:16px;border-left:3px solid #fc8181">
        <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#fc8181;margin-bottom:4px">Level 3 — HV Battery</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:#718096;margin-bottom:8px">5-day intensive; annual recertification · Lightship only · Gate 4</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.6"><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Scope:</strong> Full HV cert (NFPA 70E); crane-assisted pack swap; HV interlock procedure; recommissioning via tablet<br><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Authorization:</strong> HV battery swap — Lightship employees only, not dealer-serviceable</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Launch readiness scorecard -->
  <div class="box" style="margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="eyebrow-sm">Launch Readiness Scorecard — All Must Be GREEN Before Gate 5</div>
    <p style="font-size:11px;color:#a0aec0;margin-bottom:12px;line-height:1.6">Any RED item blocks launch. Any AMBER item requires VP Sales + VP Operations dual acceptance.</p>
