  <!-- Why this matters for WBS -->
  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:16px;margin-bottom:20px">
    <div class="box" style="border-left:3px solid #63b3ed">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm">Concept choice = WBS structure</div>
      <p style="font-size:13px;color:#cbd5e0;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:10px">The architecture decision made here determines how many control accounts exist, where the CA seams fall, which subsystem pairs must be co-owned, and how many ICD handshakes are required between teams.</p>
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:#a0aec0;line-height:1.8">
        <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:5px"><span style="color:#fc8181">Concept A:</span><span>Separate aero + structure CAs → cross-CA feedback loop on every surface change → extra ICD between CA-aero and CA-struct</span></div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:5px"><span style="color:#68d391">Concept B:</span><span>Merged aero/structure CA → internal conversation, no cross-CA ICD → cleanest WBS</span></div>
