<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     PANEL 1 — DSM LEVEL 1 COUPLING EVALUATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-1" data-panel-idx="1">
  <p class="section-intro">With the three concepts defined, we now evaluate each one's <strong style="color:#f7fafc">coupling structure</strong> using a Design Structure Matrix. The concept with the fewest cross-boundary feedback loops wins on programme risk — regardless of other trade-off criteria.</p>

  <div class="grid2" style="margin-bottom:18px">
    <div class="box">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm">Reading the DSM</div>
      <p style="font-size:13px;color:#cbd5e0;line-height:1.75">An N×N grid where element i depends on element j. A mark <strong style="color:#90cdf4">above the diagonal</strong> is sequential — clean, no rework. A mark <strong style="color:#fc8181">below the diagonal</strong> is a feedback loop — forces iteration regardless of schedule or PM process.</p>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:10px;margin-top:12px">
        <div style="background:#ebf8ff;border:1px solid #bee3f8;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;text-align:center">
          <div style="font-size:22px;color:#2b6cb0;font-weight:700;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace">→</div>
          <div style="font-size:11px;color:#2b6cb0;font-weight:600;margin-top:3px">Above diagonal</div>
          <div style="font-size:10px;color:#718096;margin-top:2px">Sequential feed-forward. Clean. No forced rework.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:#fff5f5;border:1px solid #fed7d7;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;text-align:center">
          <div style="font-size:22px;color:#c53030;font-weight:900;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace">↺</div>
          <div style="font-size:11px;color:#c53030;font-weight:600;margin-top:3px">Below diagonal</div>
          <div style="font-size:10px;color:#718096;margin-top:2px">Feedback loop. Forces iteration. Cannot be scheduled away.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
      <div class="eyebrow-sm">Why coupling is evaluated before concept selection</div>
      <p style="font-size:13px;color:#cbd5e0;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:10px">Coupling structure is an <em>input to</em> the concept decision — not a consequence of it. A concept that looks cheaper and faster at Gate 0 can be 30% over budget by Gate 3 if its coupling structure forces repeated cross-team rework cycles.</p>
      <div class="amber-alert" style="padding:10px">
        <strong style="color:#f6ad55;font-size:11px">The hidden cost of feedback loops: </strong>
        <span style="font-size:11px;color:#fbd38d">Each cross-CA feedback loop adds 2–4 weeks of rework per design iteration cycle. On a 24-month programme with 6 design cycles, a single avoidable feedback loop costs 12–24 weeks of programme schedule.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Three concept mini-matrices -->
  <div class="grid3" id="l1-cards"><!-- injected --></div>
  <div id="l1-detail"></div>

  <div class="center" style="margin-top:20px">
