    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:14px;margin-top:12px" id="concept-wbs-compare"><!-- injected --></div>
  </div>

  <div class="detail-box" style="border-color:#2f855a;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c4532,#22543d);margin-bottom:20px">
    <div style="display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:flex-start">
      <div class="icon-box">✓</div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:#68d391;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px">Gate 1 Decision</div>
        <div style="font-family:'DM Serif Display',serif;font-size:20px;color:#f0fff4;margin-bottom:8px">Concept B — Aeroshell Monocoque selected</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9ae6b4;line-height:1.75">By merging aero and structure into one composite shell, the feedback loop between the aero team and the structures team is eliminated entirely. What was a cross-CA negotiation on every design change becomes an internal conversation within one control account. Concept B achieves the best Cd (0.26), zero DSM feedback loops, and the cleanest WBS — 5 CAs vs 6 for A and 7 for C.</p>
        <div class="blue-alert mt12" style="background:rgba(26,54,93,.6)">
          <strong style="color:#63b3ed">What unlocks: </strong>
          <span style="font-size:12px;color:#90cdf4">With the architecture frozen, the Level 2 DSM can now be built against the <em>actual subsystems</em> of the chosen architecture. Those cluster boundaries directly define the WBS control account seams.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
