          <div style="font-size:12px;color:#cbd5e0;line-height:1.75">
            <div style="margin-bottom:8px;display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:flex-start"><span class="step-counter">1</span><span><strong style="color:#f7fafc">100% rule</strong> — Every deliverable must appear. Nothing outside the WBS gets budget or schedule.</span></div>
            <div style="margin-bottom:8px;display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:flex-start"><span class="step-counter">2</span><span><strong style="color:#f7fafc">Mutually exclusive</strong> — No overlap between WPs. Overlapping packages create ambiguous accountability.</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:flex-start"><span class="step-counter">3</span><span><strong style="color:#f7fafc">CA = DSM cluster</strong> — Control account seams follow cluster boundaries. Never split a coupled pair across two CAs.</span></div>
