          <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;align-items:center"><div style="width:28px;height:3px;background:#f6ad55;flex-shrink:0;border-radius:2px"></div><div><strong style="color:#f6ad55">Actual Cost (AC)</strong> — What you actually spent to date. This alone tells you nothing — you need EV to interpret it.</div></div>
          <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;margin-bottom:12px;align-items:center"><div style="width:28px;height:3px;background:#68d391;flex-shrink:0;border-radius:2px"></div><div><strong style="color:#68d391">Earned Value (EV)</strong> — Budgeted cost of the work actually completed. This is the key number.</div></div>
          <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">
