        <div style="background:#1a202c;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:12px">
          <div style="margin-bottom:8px;padding-bottom:8px;border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748"><span style="color:#718096">Pessimistic: </span><span style="color:#f7fafc">EAC = BAC ÷ CPI</span><div style="font-size:10px;color:#4a5568;margin-top:2px">Assumes current efficiency continues to end</div></div>
          <div style="margin-bottom:8px;padding-bottom:8px;border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748"><span style="color:#718096">Optimistic: </span><span style="color:#f7fafc">EAC = AC + (BAC − EV)</span><div style="font-size:10px;color:#4a5568;margin-top:2px">Assumes remaining work will be done on plan</div></div>
          <div><span style="color:#718096">L1 EAC (pessimistic): </span><span style="color:#fc8181;font-weight:700">$14.1M</span><div style="font-size:10px;color:#4a5568;margin-top:2px">BAC $13.3M ÷ CPI 0.94 = $14.1M — $0.8M overrun forecast</div></div>
