      <div class="insight" style="max-width:none">
        <div class="label">WHY EVM NEEDS THE WBS</div>
        <p style="margin-bottom:8px">EVM only works if you can measure % complete at the work package level. Without a WBS, "% complete" is a subjective guess — the infamous 90% complete that stays at 90% for months. With a WBS, % complete is measured by task closure: 7 of 10 tasks closed = 70% (by count) or by earned hours vs planned hours.</p>
        <p>The WBS dictionary defines the 100% completion criteria for each WP — the precise condition under which a task is counted as done. Without this, earned value is meaningless.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
